Data Wrangling

Create a dataframe of stats for every game every team plays. Each game is in twice.

regular = 


  data %>%


    rename(TeamID=WTeamID, Score=WScore, OPTeamID=LTeamID,OPScore = LScore, LOC=WLoc,


         NumOT = NumOT, FGM = WFGM,FGA = WFGA,FGM3=WFGM3, FGA3=WFGA3, FTM=WFTM,FTA=WFTA,


         OR=WOR,DR = WDR, Ast=WAst,TO=WTO,Stl=WStl,Blk=WBlk,PF=WPF,OPFGM = LFGM,OPFGA=LFGA,


         OPFGM3=LFGM3,OPFGA3=LFGA3,OPFTM=LFTM,OPFTA=LFTA,OPOR=LOR,OPDR=LDR,OPAst=LAst,


         OPTO=LTO,OPStl=LStl,OPBlk=LBlk,OPPF=LPF) %>%


    mutate(Win = 1) %>%


  


  bind_rows(


    


    data %>%


      rename(TeamID=LTeamID, Score=LScore, OPTeamID=WTeamID,OPScore = WScore, LOC=WLoc,


             NumOT = NumOT, FGM = LFGM,FGA = LFGA,FGM3=LFGM3, FGA3=LFGA3, FTM=LFTM,FTA=LFTA,


             OR=LOR,DR = LDR, Ast=LAst,TO=LTO,Stl=LStl,Blk=LBlk,PF=LPF,OPFGM = WFGM,OPFGA=WFGA,


             OPFGM3=WFGM3,OPFGA3=WFGA3,OPFTM=WFTM,OPFTA=WFTA,OPOR=WOR,OPDR=WDR,OPAst=WAst,


             OPTO=WTO,OPStl=WStl,OPBlk=WBlk,OPPF=WPF) %>%


      mutate(Win = 0, LOC = ifelse(LOC=="H","A",ifelse(LOC=="A","H",LOC)))


    ) %>%


  mutate(TeamID = as.factor(TeamID),OPTeamID = as.factor(OPTeamID), LOC = as.factor(LOC)) %>%


  filter(Season == "2018")

Create a rolling mean of points scored and opponents points scored

regular = 


  regular %>% group_by(TeamID) %>%


  mutate(ScoreMean3 = rollmean(Score,3, fill = NA, align = "right")) %>%


  mutate(OPScoreMean3 = rollmean(OPScore,3, fill = NA, align = "right")) %>%


  mutate(scorediff3 = ScoreMean3-OPScoreMean3) %>%


  mutate(ScoreMean5 = rollmean(Score,5, fill = NA, align = "right")) %>%


  mutate(OPScoreMean5 = rollmean(OPScore,5, fill = NA, align = "right")) %>%


  mutate(scorediff5 = ScoreMean5-OPScoreMean5)

Create season stats from game stats

sregular = regular %>% group_by(TeamID) %>%


  summarise(SScore = mean(Score), 


            SOPScore = mean(OPScore), 


            SFGM = mean(FGM), SFGA = mean(FGA), 


            SFTM = mean(FTM), SFTA = mean(FTA),


            SOR = mean(OR), SDR = mean(DR), 


            SDR = mean(DR), SAst = mean(Ast), 


            STO = mean(TO), SStl = mean(Stl), 


            SBlk = mean(Blk), SPF = mean(PF), 


            OPSFGM = mean(OPFGM), OPSFGA = mean(OPFGA), 


            OPSFTM = mean(OPFTM), OPSFTA = mean(OPFTA),


            OPSOR = mean(OPOR), OPSDR = mean(OPDR), 


            OPSDR = mean(OPDR), OPSAst = mean(OPAst), 


            OPSTO = mean(OPTO), OPSStl = mean(OPStl), 


            OPSBlk = mean(OPBlk), OPSPF = mean(OPPF), 


            winpct = sum(Win)/n()*100 ) %>%


  ungroup()

A Brief Aside on Clustering

Cluster Teams by Similarity of Statistics

bet = NA


betw =NA


for (i in 1:15) {


  km.out = kmeans(sregular[, c(-1)], i, nstart = 20)


  bet[i] = km.out$betweenss / (km.out$tot.withinss + km.out$betweenss)


  betw[i] = km.out$tot.withinss


}


plot(x=1:15,y=bet)

plot(x=1:15,y=betw)

km.out.final=kmeans(sregular[,c(-1)],8,nstart = 20)

Add clusters to regular season and seasonlong dataframes

joining = data.frame(sregular,clusterwin = km.out.final$cluster, clusterloss = km.out.final$cluster)




regwcluster = regular %>%


  left_join(as.tibble(joining[,c(1,27)]), by = c("TeamID"="TeamID")) %>%


  left_join(as.tibble(joining[,c(1,28)]), by = c("OPTeamID"="TeamID"))




sregular  = sregular %>%


  left_join(as.tibble(joining[,c(1,27)]), by = c("TeamID"="TeamID"))

Create Model for predicting how many points a team will score against a specific opponent

linmod1 = lm(Score~TeamID+as.factor(clusterwin)*as.factor(clusterloss), data = regwcluster)


linmod2 = lm(OPScore~OPTeamID+as.factor(clusterwin)*as.factor(clusterloss), data = regwcluster)

Probability Team A Beats Team B

sum(game1a>game1b)/length(game1a)
## [1] 0.1495

Do this for every game

probvec = NA


for (i in 1:nrow(tournament)) {


  game1a = rnorm(10000,predictions1[i,1],(predictions1[i,1]-predictions1[i,2])/1.96)


  game1b = rnorm(10000,predictions2[i,1],(predictions2[i,1]-predictions2[i,2])/1.96)


  probvec[i] = sum(game1a>game1b)/length(game1a)


}

An Example of What Just Happened

Who are these teams anyway?

Simulate Bracket

Join data together

forespnhelp = as.tibble(data.frame(tournamen, tourny))




forespn =


  forespnhelp %>%


  left_join(teams, by = c("TeamID" = "TeamID")) %>% select(-FirstD1Season,-LastD1Season) %>%


  left_join(teams, by = c("OPTeamID" = "TeamID")) %>% select(-FirstD1Season,-LastD1Season) %>% rename(TeamName = TeamName.x, OPTeamName = TeamName.y)

Hardcode Teams in the order of the bracket

Round 1

Have all teams play each other 1000 times

round1 = NULL


for (i in seq(1,length(teamvec)-1,2)) {


test = forespn %>%


  filter(TeamName==teamvec[i] & OPTeamName==teamvec[i+1] | TeamName==teamvec[i+1] & OPTeamName==teamvec[i])


game1 = ifelse(runif(10000)<test$Pred,test$TeamName,test$OPTeamName)


round1 = cbind(round1,game1)


}

      filter(TeamName == round3[i, j] & OPTeamName == round3[i, j + 1] | TeamName == round3[i, j + 1] & OPTeamName == round3[i, j])


    temp[i] = ifelse(runif(1) < test$Pred, test$TeamName, test$OPTeamName)


  }


  round4 = cbind(round4, temp)


}

Join All The Simulated Rounds Together

results =


  as.data.frame(table(round1) / 100) %>%


  rename(Freq1 = Freq) %>%


  left_join(


    as.data.frame(table(round2) / 100) %>%


      rename(Freq2 = Freq) %>%


      left_join(


        as.data.frame(table(round3) / 100) %>%


          rename(Freq3 = Freq) %>%


          left_join(


            as.data.frame(table(round4) / 100) %>%


              rename(Freq4 = Freq) %>%


              left_join(


                as.data.frame(table(round5) / 100) %>%


                  rename(Freq5 = Freq) %>%


                  left_join(


                    as.data.frame(table(round6) / 100) %>%


                      rename(Freq6 = Freq),


                    by = c("round5" = "round6")


                  ),


                by = c("round4" = "round5")


              ),


            by = c("round3" = "round4")


          ),


        by = c("round2" = "round3")


      ),


    by = c("round1" = "round2")


  ) %>%


  replace_na(list(Freq5 = 0, Freq6 = 0)) %>%


  arrange(!is.na(Freq6), Freq6) 




colnames(results) = c("Team","Top 32","Sweet 16","Elite 8","Final 4","Final 2","Winner")




results$Team = with(results, reorder(Team,Winner))




results = results %>% as.tibble() %>%


replace_na(list("Sweet 16" = c(0),"Elite 8" = c(0),"Final 4" = c(0))) %>%


  as.data.frame()
